{
  "video_id": "b3Ysh6IQ6dc",
  "title": "The World's Strangest Borders Part 1: Panhandles",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 500.0,
      "end_time": 3160.0,
      "text": "Countries in the world come in all different shapes and sizes."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3160.0,
      "end_time": 5190.0,
      "text": "Some are huge, while others are tiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5190.0,
      "end_time": 7020.0,
      "text": "And then some have very clearly defined"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 7020.0,
      "end_time": 10170.0,
      "text": "shapes, like these, and others, well, not so much."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10170.0,
      "end_time": 12000.0,
      "text": "Borders are a funny thing and don&#39;t often"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12000.0,
      "end_time": 14730.0,
      "text": "make sense without some historical or geographical"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14730.0,
      "end_time": 15540.0,
      "text": "context."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 15540.0,
      "end_time": 18630.0,
      "text": "Sometimes borders take on an exceptionally bizarre look,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 18630.0,
      "end_time": 20970.0,
      "text": "extending away from the home country like a tentacle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 20970.0,
      "end_time": 22350.0,
      "text": "or an extra limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 22350.0,
      "end_time": 24510.0,
      "text": "This is called a panhandle, or a salient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 24510.0,
      "end_time": 27120.0,
      "text": "and we are going to look at five of the strangest examples"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 27120.0,
      "end_time": 29100.0,
      "text": "of these from around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 29100.0,
      "end_time": 30600.0,
      "text": "To begin with, we&#39;re going to Italy"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 30600.0,
      "end_time": 33690.0,
      "text": "to look at this example, the province of Trieste."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 33690.0,
      "end_time": 37050.0,
      "text": "This province extends 48 kilometers, or 30 miles down"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 37050.0,
      "end_time": 39810.0,
      "text": "the coast away from Italy and into Slovenia."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 39810.0,
      "end_time": 42840.0,
      "text": "History is the reason why this situation exists today."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 42840.0,
      "end_time": 44610.0,
      "text": "Basically this entire territory used"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 44610.0,
      "end_time": 46710.0,
      "text": "to be a part of the Austro-Hungarian empire."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 46710.0,
      "end_time": 48960.0,
      "text": "And outside of Battlefield 1, nobody has ever"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 48960.0,
      "end_time": 50520.0,
      "text": "heard that name in a very long time"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 50520.0,
      "end_time": 53010.0,
      "text": "because World War I happened, and Italy took over a bunch"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 53010.0,
      "end_time": 54990.0,
      "text": "of their land after winning."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 54990.0,
      "end_time": 58111.0,
      "text": "But then Mussolini happened, and Italy lost World War II"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 58111.0,
      "end_time": 60360.0,
      "text": "and, therefore, lost pretty much all of that territory"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 60360.0,
      "end_time": 62160.0,
      "text": "that they had won in the first war."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 62160.0,
      "end_time": 65099.0,
      "text": "Trieste became an independent city-state under UN protection"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 65099.00000000001,
      "end_time": 68710.0,
      "text": "in 1947, but that only lasted until 1954,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 68710.0,
      "end_time": 70680.0,
      "text": "when the tiny country&#39;s territory was divided"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 70680.0,
      "end_time": 72870.0,
      "text": "between Italy and Yugoslavia."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 72870.0,
      "end_time": 75270.0,
      "text": "The part that Italy occupied in 1954"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 75270.0,
      "end_time": 77910.0,
      "text": "remains the border of today, and that is why the border here"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 77910.0,
      "end_time": 79470.0,
      "text": "looks so odd."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 79470.0,
      "end_time": 81960.0,
      "text": "Next up at number four, we are going pretty far away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 81960.0,
      "end_time": 84720.0,
      "text": "to India, which looks mostly normal, except for this mesh"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 84720.0,
      "end_time": 86010.0,
      "text": "over here in the east."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 86010.0,
      "end_time": 88680.0,
      "text": "Zooming in a little closer, we can see that this side of India"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 88680.0,
      "end_time": 90210.0,
      "text": "and this side of India is connected"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 90210.0,
      "end_time": 93210.0,
      "text": "by only a very tiny sliver of land known as the Siliguri"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 93210.0,
      "end_time": 94170.0,
      "text": "Corridor."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 94170.0,
      "end_time": 96240.0,
      "text": "This awkward situation, like every other entry"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 96240.0,
      "end_time": 98580.0,
      "text": "on this list from here on out, came about as a result"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 98580.0,
      "end_time": 99900.0,
      "text": "from colonialism."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 99900.0,
      "end_time": 102150.0,
      "text": "When India gained independence from the United Kingdom"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 102150.0,
      "end_time": 105840.0,
      "text": "in 1947, the British decided to partition India between a Hindu"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 105840.0,
      "end_time": 107009.0,
      "text": "part and a Muslim part."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 107009.0,
      "end_time": 109050.0,
      "text": "Pakistan became the Muslim part and, at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 109050.0,
      "end_time": 112350.0,
      "text": "consisted of West Pakistan here and East Pakistan here."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 112350.0,
      "end_time": 115540.0,
      "text": "Pakistan was separated by all of India from her two halves."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 115540.0,
      "end_time": 117000.0,
      "text": "And the Northeast of India was only"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 117000.0,
      "end_time": 119040.0,
      "text": "connected by the Siliguri Corridor."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 119040.0,
      "end_time": 121920.0,
      "text": "At one point, the corridor is not even 27 kilometers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 121920.0,
      "end_time": 123960.0,
      "text": "or 17 miles, wide."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 123960.0,
      "end_time": 126960.0,
      "text": "The Indian state of Sikkim extends north of the corridor"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 126960.0,
      "end_time": 128820.0,
      "text": "and separates Nepal from Bhutan."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 128820.0,
      "end_time": 130949.0,
      "text": "And they connects to the seven other Indian states"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 130949.00000000001,
      "end_time": 134100.0,
      "text": "in the east, with a population of almost 45 million people"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 134100.0,
      "end_time": 135090.0,
      "text": "between them."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 135090.0,
      "end_time": 137337.0,
      "text": "So 45 million Indians are connected"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 137337.0,
      "end_time": 139920.0,
      "text": "to the rest of their country by a corridor that, at one point,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 139920.0,
      "end_time": 142890.0,
      "text": "is only 27 kilometers long."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 142890.0,
      "end_time": 145320.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to move slightly up north to Afghanistan"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 145320.0,
      "end_time": 146670.0,
      "text": "for our next example."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 146670.0,
      "end_time": 149400.0,
      "text": "Much like how an appendix serves no clear purpose to humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 149400.0,
      "end_time": 151830.0,
      "text": "any longer, the Wakhan corridor in Afghanistan"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 151830.0,
      "end_time": 153480.0,
      "text": "seems like it makes no sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 153480.0,
      "end_time": 156360.0,
      "text": "It is a part of Afghanistan that stretches out for a very long"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 156360.0,
      "end_time": 159862.0,
      "text": "350 kilometers, or 220 miles, away"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 159862.0,
      "end_time": 161070.0,
      "text": "from the rest of the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 161070.0,
      "end_time": 164370.0,
      "text": "In width, the corridor varies from between just 13 kilometers"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 164370.0,
      "end_time": 167790.0,
      "text": "to 65 kilometers, or 8 to 40 miles."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 167790.0,
      "end_time": 170460.0,
      "text": "The corridor means that Afghanistan shares a tiny land"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 170460.0,
      "end_time": 173520.0,
      "text": "border with China and completely separates Tajikistan"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 173520.0,
      "end_time": 174614.0,
      "text": "from Pakistan."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 174614.0,
      "end_time": 177030.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t make much sense now, but pushing the clock back"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 177030.0,
      "end_time": 180030.0,
      "text": "over a century explains why it exists today."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 180030.0,
      "end_time": 182850.0,
      "text": "In the 19th century, the Russian and British empires"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 182850.0,
      "end_time": 184710.0,
      "text": "were both competing for territory here."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 184710.0,
      "end_time": 187440.0,
      "text": "Russia ruled Central Asia, and Britain ruled India."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 187440.0,
      "end_time": 190350.0,
      "text": "To settle a dispute between either empire gaining more land"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 190350.0,
      "end_time": 192120.0,
      "text": "and influence in the region, both"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 192120.0,
      "end_time": 194730.0,
      "text": "agreed to respect Afghanistan as an independent country that"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 194730.0,
      "end_time": 196950.0,
      "text": "would serve as a buffer region between them."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 196950.0,
      "end_time": 198960.0,
      "text": "But the borders of Afghanistan at the time"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 198960.0,
      "end_time": 201120.0,
      "text": "didn&#39;t exactly match up between the Russian"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 201120.0,
      "end_time": 202860.0,
      "text": "and the British borders, so they decided"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 202860.0,
      "end_time": 206130.0,
      "text": "to expand Afghanistan 350 kilometers east to fit"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 206130.0,
      "end_time": 207630.0,
      "text": "between the rest of the space."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 207630.0,
      "end_time": 209310.0,
      "text": "Over a century later, the corridor"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 209310.0,
      "end_time": 213120.0,
      "text": "remains, but as a border between Tajikistan and Pakistan."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 213120.0,
      "end_time": 215130.0,
      "text": "Our next two entries are both located"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 215130.0,
      "end_time": 217410.0,
      "text": "in Africa, whose colonial past is obvious"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 217410.0,
      "end_time": 219210.0,
      "text": "when you look at the continent&#39;s borders."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 219210.0,
      "end_time": 221251.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to start with the Democratic Republic"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 221251.0,
      "end_time": 224430.0,
      "text": "of the Congo, which has not one, but two, panhandles."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 224430.0,
      "end_time": 226456.0,
      "text": "The Congo used to be a colony of Belgium."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 226456.0,
      "end_time": 228330.0,
      "text": "And the Belgians created this one on the left"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 228330.0,
      "end_time": 229704.0,
      "text": "called Congo Central so that they"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 229704.0,
      "end_time": 232390.0,
      "text": "could access their enormous colony from the ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 232390.0,
      "end_time": 234990.0,
      "text": "The second down here is called the Congo pedicle."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 234990.0,
      "end_time": 237570.0,
      "text": "It cuts between 200 kilometers into Zambia"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 237570.0,
      "end_time": 241110.0,
      "text": "and varies between 70 to 100 kilometers wide."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 241110.0,
      "end_time": 243480.0,
      "text": "The pedicle is even more awkward than it looks."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 243480.0,
      "end_time": 246090.0,
      "text": "Basically, back when the Congo was a Belgian colony"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 246090.0,
      "end_time": 248400.0,
      "text": "and Zambia was a British colony, the two sides"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 248400.0,
      "end_time": 250860.0,
      "text": "could not agree on the colonial borders."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 250860.0,
      "end_time": 253380.0,
      "text": "The Belgians wanted access to the rich swamplands here"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 253380.0,
      "end_time": 255150.0,
      "text": "that had a lot of wildlife they could hunt"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 255150.0,
      "end_time": 256440.0,
      "text": "for their precious trophies."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 256440.0,
      "end_time": 258029.0,
      "text": "So the two sides got the King of Italy"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 258029.0,
      "end_time": 260040.0,
      "text": "to intervene and draw the border for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 260040.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261510.00000000003,
      "text": "Knowing about as much about Africa"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 261510.0,
      "end_time": 263640.0,
      "text": "as you would expect of a man in the 19th century"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 263640.0,
      "end_time": 265140.0,
      "text": "before the internet, the King just"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 265140.0,
      "end_time": 266670.0,
      "text": "drew a line on a map in front of him"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 266670.0,
      "end_time": 267900.0,
      "text": "and decided that it looked good."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 267900.0,
      "end_time": 269610.0,
      "text": "And the two other sides thought that it looked good enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 269610.0,
      "end_time": 271050.0,
      "text": "and, boom, there was the border."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 271050.0,
      "end_time": 272580.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s still there today."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 272580.0,
      "end_time": 274524.0,
      "text": "Finally, and perhaps most bizarrely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 274524.0,
      "end_time": 275940.0,
      "text": "we have the case of Namibia, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 275940.0,
      "end_time": 278820.0,
      "text": "has this absurd protrusion in the Northeast of the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 278820.0,
      "end_time": 281010.0,
      "text": "This extension is called the Caprivi strip,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 281010.0,
      "end_time": 284850.0,
      "text": "and it goes for 450 kilometers or 280 miles away"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 284850.0,
      "end_time": 286170.0,
      "text": "from the rest of Namibia."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 286170.0,
      "end_time": 290850.0,
      "text": "This bizarre border exists because, between 1884 and 1915,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 290850.0,
      "end_time": 292560.0,
      "text": "Namibia was a colony of Germany."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 292560.0,
      "end_time": 294360.0,
      "text": "In 1890, the chancellor of Germany"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 294360.0,
      "end_time": 297210.0,
      "text": "named Leo Von Caprivi, for whom the strip is named after,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 297210.0,
      "end_time": 299880.0,
      "text": "wanted of the colony&#39;s border to extend to the Zambezi River"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 299880.0,
      "end_time": 301800.0,
      "text": "here so that Germany could navigate the river"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 301800.0,
      "end_time": 303540.0,
      "text": "to the African east coast."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 303540.0,
      "end_time": 305070.0,
      "text": "In a treaty with Britain, Germany"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 305070.0,
      "end_time": 307960.0,
      "text": "gave up all colonial claims to the territory of Zanzibar"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 307960.0,
      "end_time": 309690.0,
      "text": "and, in exchange, was granted the strip,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 309690.0,
      "end_time": 311130.0,
      "text": "stretching hundreds of kilometers"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 311130.0,
      "end_time": 312396.0,
      "text": "across the continent."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 312396.0,
      "end_time": 313770.0,
      "text": "It makes less sense when you look"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 313770.0,
      "end_time": 315840.0,
      "text": "at an actual ethnic map of Africa, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 315840.0,
      "end_time": 317320.0,
      "text": "roughly looks like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 317320.0,
      "end_time": 320310.0,
      "text": "As you can see, the strip covers numerous ethnic and linguistic"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 320310.0,
      "end_time": 322740.0,
      "text": "groups that were not taken into any consideration prior"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 322740.0,
      "end_time": 323820.0,
      "text": "to the decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 323820.0,
      "end_time": 325620.0,
      "text": "Today the existence of the strip means"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 325620.0,
      "end_time": 327990.0,
      "text": "that Botswana is almost entirely blocked off"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 327990.0,
      "end_time": 330690.0,
      "text": "from bordering Zambia, other than a very tiny opening"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 330690.0,
      "end_time": 332160.0,
      "text": "on the Zambezi River here."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 332160.0,
      "end_time": 335610.0,
      "text": "And Namibia almost borders Zimbabwe, just 200 meters down"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 335610.0,
      "end_time": 336600.0,
      "text": "the same river."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 336600.0,
      "end_time": 338850.0,
      "text": "There were a lot of other strange borders in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 338850.0,
      "end_time": 340950.0,
      "text": "to be covered, but that&#39;s all for now."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 340950.0,
      "end_time": 342930.0,
      "text": "Leave your comments below about what you think"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 342930.0,
      "end_time": 344610.0,
      "text": "are the strangest international borders."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
